headline: Morgan Stanley price target lowered to $130 from $142 at Wells Fargo
summary: Wells Fargo lowered the firm’s price target on Morgan Stanley (MS) to $130 from $142 and keeps an Equal Weight rating on the shares as part of a Q1 earnings preview for the large-cap banks. The firm is bullish on the sector on a one-year view citing the “biggest deregulation in three decades,” but note that Q1 outlooks “may be tricky” given policy uncertainties.
